<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/35:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Travers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-01T23:00:00+01:00">September
                                    1, 1939—11 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 1—7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>173. Conditions in Hungary calm and no great military movements visible.
                            The Chief of the Political Section of the Foreign Office reiterated
                            tonight to me that Hungary’s hands are still free and that Hungary will
                            never fight Poland. He envisages Hungary maintaining neutrality for some
                            time to come and said it is probable that a strict censorship will soon
                            be imposed in order to assist in maintaining that neutrality.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Travers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>